Russia’s RTS Stock-Index Futures Rise on Metals, $100 Crude Oil

-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 
2011-03-03T17:11:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-03/russia-s-rts-stock-index-futures-rise-on-metals-100-crude-oil.html
  Russia ’s RTS stock-index futures
gained 0.1 percent at the start of trading as metals climbed and
oil, the country’s main export earner, traded above $100 a
barrel.  Futures on the dollar-denominated index expiring in March
added 0.1 percent to 200,955 at 11:45 a.m. in  New York .  Contracts on OAO Sberbank, Russia’s largest lender, gained
0.3 percent. Futures on OAO Lukoil, the country’s second-biggest
oil producer, rose 0.1 percent. The Market Vectors Russia ETF, a
U.S.-traded fund that holds Russian shares, climbed 0.3 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Halia Pavliva in New York at 
